---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About — A Med Student's Honest Guide to Board Prep"
  description="USMLE Prep Guide is built by a medical student who's been through the trenches. Real advice, real experience, no fluff."
>
  <Header />

  <main class="container">
    <article class="about">
      <div class="about-header">
        <div class="avatar">S</div>
        <div>
          <h1>Hey, I'm a real med student.</h1>
          <p class="subtitle">And I built this because I wish it existed when I started.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="about-body">
        <h2>Why this site exists</h2>
        <p>
          When I started prepping for boards, I spent <strong>weeks</strong> just figuring out
          what to study with. Every forum thread contradicted the last one. Reddit said use Anking.
          My upperclassman said skip Anki entirely. One blog ranked UWorld #1, another said Amboss
          was better. Nobody agreed on anything.
        </p>
        <p>
          I wasted time I didn't have.
        </p>
        <p>
          So I built USMLE Prep Guide to be the resource I wish I'd had — <strong>one place</strong>
          with honest, experience-backed advice on what actually works, what's overrated, and how to
          build a study plan that doesn't fall apart at week 3.
        </p>

        <h2>What makes this different</h2>
        <p>
          This isn't a corporate content farm. I'm a med student writing about what I've actually
          used, what my classmates swear by, and what the data says. Every recommendation comes
          from real experience in the trenches — not a marketing team.
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Honest reviews</strong> — if a $400 qbank isn't worth it, I'll say so</li>
          <li><strong>Practical schedules</strong> — built around how students actually study, not how we wish we did</li>
          <li><strong>No gatekeeping</strong> — the best resources and strategies, explained clearly</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>The deal with affiliate links</h2>
        <p>
          Some links on this site are affiliate links. If you buy something through them, I might
          earn a small commission — at zero extra cost to you. It helps keep this site running.
          But I'll never recommend something I wouldn't use myself. That's a promise.
        </p>
        <p>
          Full details on our <a href="/disclaimer">disclaimer page</a>.
        </p>

        <h2>Currently</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Surviving medical school one Anki review at a time</li>
          <li>Maintaining a questionable relationship with First Aid</li>
          <li>Trying to convince myself that "just one more UWorld block" is a good idea at 11 PM</li>
        </ul>

        <p class="closing">
          If anything on this site helps you score even a few points higher — or saves you from
          buying a resource you don't need — then it was worth building.
        </p>
        <p class="closing">
          Good luck out there. You've got this.
        </p>
      </div>
    </article>
  </main>

  <Footer />
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .about {
    padding: 2.5rem 0 4rem;
    max-width: 680px;
  }

  .about-header {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 1.25rem;
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
    padding-bottom: 2rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  .avatar {
    width: 64px;
    height: 64px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, #1d4ed8 0%, #1e3a8a 100%);
    color: #fff;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    font-weight: 800;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  .about-header h1 {
    font-size: 1.75rem;
    font-weight: 800;
    margin: 0 0 0.25rem;
    line-height: 1.2;
  }

  .subtitle {
    color: var(--color-muted);
    margin: 0;
    font-size: 1.05rem;
  }

  .about-body h2 {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    margin: 2rem 0 0.75rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    padding-bottom: 0.35rem;
  }

  .about-body p {
    margin: 0 0 1rem;
    line-height: 1.75;
  }

  .about-body ul {
    margin: 0 0 1.25rem 1.5rem;
    line-height: 1.75;
  }

  .about-body li {
    margin-bottom: 0.4rem;
  }

  .closing {
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    font-weight: 500;
  }
</style>
